## 4. System Description

SoilSense is an IoT platform designed for environmental monitoring and remote control.

The system consists of:

* ESP32-C6 sensor nodes
* Humidity sensors
* Temperature sensors
* Water level sensor
* Pump actuator
* Gateway node
* OpenThread Border Router
* Matter Controller
* Web/Mobile Dashboard

Sensor nodes collect environmental data and publish information through the network. Data is processed and delivered to the dashboard where users can visualize real-time measurements, review historical information, receive alerts, and control actuators.

---

## 5. Business Goals

The primary business goals of SoilSense are:

### Continuous Monitoring

Provide permanent visibility of critical environmental variables.

### Operational Efficiency

Reduce the need for manual inspections and repetitive monitoring tasks.

### Faster Decision Making

Enable users to react quickly to environmental changes through real-time information.

### Remote Operation

Allow monitoring and control without requiring physical presence.

### Data Traceability

Maintain historical records for analysis and future decision-making.

### Scalability

Support the integration of additional sensor nodes and services without redesigning the architecture.

### Interoperability

Use open standards to facilitate future integrations and avoid vendor lock-in.

---

## 6. Value Proposition

SoilSense transforms environmental measurements into actionable information.

The platform provides:

* Real-time monitoring
* Historical data analysis
* Automatic alerts
* Remote actuator control
* Continuous visibility of system status
* Self-healing network infrastructure

These capabilities improve operational awareness and support data-driven decision making.

---

## 7. Service Blueprint

### User Interaction Layer

The user accesses the system through a web or mobile dashboard.

Available services include:

* Real-time visualization
* Historical data review
* Alert management
* Actuator control

### Application Layer

The Matter Controller manages device integration, state synchronization, and command distribution.

### Communication Layer

The system uses:

* MQTT between sensor nodes and gateway
* CoAP for device communication
* DTLS for secure communication
* OpenThread for IPv6 mesh networking

### Physical Layer

ESP32-C6 devices interact with the physical environment through sensors and actuators.

