## 10. Business Risks

| Risk                        | Potential Impact                          |
| --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| Connectivity Failure        | Delayed monitoring and control            |
| Sensor Failure              | Incorrect information for decision making |
| Actuator Failure            | Inability to execute corrective actions   |
| Unauthorized Access         | Security and operational risks            |
| External Service Dependency | Reduced functionality during outages      |

---

## 11. Mitigation Strategies

* Secure communications through DTLS.
* Validation of sensor data before processing.
* Definition of safe actuator states.
* Network self-recovery through OpenThread.
* Use of open standards and interoperable technologies.
* Periodic testing and maintenance procedures.

---

## 12. Conclusion

The SoilSense architecture generates business value by combining real-time monitoring, historical analysis, remote control, and interoperable IoT technologies.

From a business perspective, the system improves operational efficiency, enhances decision-making capabilities, reduces manual effort, and provides a scalable foundation for future growth.

The adoption of MQTT, CoAP, OpenThread, Matter, and ESP32-C6 devices supports a sustainable and extensible architecture aligned with the principles of the ISO/IEC 30141 Business Viewpoint.
